sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Boeing Co. (Symbol: BA), where a total volume of 36,551 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.7 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 80.1% of BA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $410 strike call option expiring February 15, 2019 , with 5,955 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 595,500 underlying shares of BA.

Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 36,635 contracts, representing approximately 3.7 million underlying shares or approximately 74.1% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.9 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $160 strike call option expiring February 15, 2019 , with 3,656 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 365,600 underlying shares of CRM.

Especially high volume was seen for the $1150 strike call option expiring February 15, 2019 , with 1,099 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 109,900 underlying shares of GOOG.
